column5: Looking for a place to buy 10" plus suckers on the way up to huntsville, So barrie, orillia, bracebridge ect.  I know there is a guy in Norland but im sure there is a place more enroute.  Thanks
Ellwood Epps on 11 North, North of Orillia, Jacob's (sp?) on 11 North, South of Orillia, usually have stock to the best of my knowledge.  Michael
I've bought some from Rack 'n Reel in Barrie before for winter pike.
Thanks I'll google and give them a call
Question - They still open?  I've had a number of people tell me it was locked up no matter when they went there.  Michael
ellwood epps!!! I always stop by there on the way up to the cottage!!!

You know what...I'm not really sure. Everytime I drive by they look like they are. I've been hitting up Tromblys Tacklebox this summer on the way to the kawarthas so I haven't been to Rack n' reel since winter.
